5.2 Required Modified-Version Notice

Every External Disclosure must clearly and reasonably prominently state that the
material or software is modified and unofficial. It must include the following
notice, or a substantially equivalent notice that preserves its full meaning:

"This is or depicts a modified and unofficial version of Ksword5.1. The
modifications and related statements are solely those of the modifier or
distributor and do not represent the views, positions, opinions, statements, or
endorsements of WangWei-CM / OB_BUFF(Felix3322), the copyright holder, or the
original Ksword5.1 project maintainers."

For a screenshot, post, short clip, or similar item, the notice may appear in a
clearly visible caption, overlay, description, or immediately accompanying text.
For a video, livestream, article, report, presentation, or download page, the
notice must appear in the content, description, credits, documentation, legal
notices, or another location an ordinary viewer or recipient can readily find.
The notice must not be hidden, intentionally obscured, rendered unreadable, or
placed where recipients are unlikely to find it.

5.3 Additional Requirements for Distribution of a Modified Version

You may redistribute a Modified Version without separate Formal Written
Authorization only free of charge, provided that You comply with the no-Copy-Charge,
source-code, license, attribution, distributor-identification, independent-status,
and no-false-authorship requirements of Section 4 and all requirements of this
Section, including the following:

- clearly identify Yourself or Your organization as the modifier and
  distributor;
- provide complete Corresponding Source for the exact Modified Version at no
  charge under the same conditions stated in Section 4;
- include a readily accessible MODIFICATIONS, CHANGES, or CHANGELOG file, or an
  equivalent written notice;
- identify the files, modules, components, features, or behavior materially
  changed;
- meaningfully describe what was added, removed, replaced, patched, or otherwise
  modified;
- state the relevant modification date or version and the identity of the
  modifier; and
- disclose any known material compatibility, security, or behavioral
  differences caused by the modifications.

A vague statement such as "modified version", "custom build", or "various
changes" is not sufficient by itself. The disclosure must contain enough
information for a reasonable recipient to distinguish the modifications from
the original Software.

Where reasonably practicable, modified source files distributed to others must
carry a notice stating that they were changed, together with a relevant date or
version and the identity of the modifier.

You may use a different product name for a Modified Version, but You must still
identify it as derived from Ksword5.1, preserve the required attribution, and
avoid any implication that it is an official release.

The modifier or distributor is solely responsible for its modifications,
representations, warranties, support commitments, security claims, and any
